<section class="section">

<h2>
Research <span>Overview</span>
</h2>

<p>
Lipid profiling is a foundational approach in lipidomics. It measures diverse lipid species such as phospholipids, sphingolipids, glycerolipids, sterols, fatty acids, and lipid mediators to understand cellular structure, metabolism, signaling, and disease biology.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, lipid profiling is presented as a core lipidomics research area: the starting point for membrane biology, metabolic regulation, inflammation signaling, disease biomarker discovery, and multi-omics systems interpretation.
</p>

</section>

